headline: RJF Q4 Deep Dive: Adviser Recruiting and Lending Fuel Growth Amid Market Pressures
summary: Financial services firm Raymond James Financial (NYSE:RJF) fell short of the markets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, but sales rose 5.6% year on year to $3.74 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.86 per share was 1.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
